<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-10-24T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-10-24T15:00:00-05:00" n="836" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d836">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">693.003/915: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-10-24T15:00:00-05:00">October 24, 1929—3
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>347. Your 903, October 18, 5 p.m. The Department does not perceive from
                            your telegram that any reasons exist for protesting against the
                            application of the new procedure.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
